#!/bin/bash
# tinker-cleanup — runs nightly via cron
# Releases ports that haven't been used in 7 days
# Install: cp tinker-cleanup /etc/cron.daily/tinker-cleanup && chmod 755 /etc/cron.daily/tinker-cleanup

PORTS_FILE="/var/tinker/ports/ports"
CADDY_DIR="/var/tinker/caddy"
EXPIRY_DAYS=7
NOW=$(date +%s)
EXPIRY_SECS=$((EXPIRY_DAYS * 86400))

[[ -f "$PORTS_FILE" ]] || exit 0

changed=0
tmpfile=$(mktemp)

while read -r user port timestamp; do
  age=$((NOW - timestamp))
  # Check if port is currently in use
  if ss -tlnp | grep -q ":$port "; then
    # Port active — update timestamp
    echo "$user $port $NOW" >> "$tmpfile"
  elif [[ $age -lt $EXPIRY_SECS ]]; then
    # Not expired yet — keep
    echo "$user $port $timestamp" >> "$tmpfile"
  else
    # Expired — release
    echo "Releasing port $port for user $user (inactive for $((age/86400)) days)"
    rm -f "$CADDY_DIR/${user}-"*.conf
    changed=1
  fi
done < "$PORTS_FILE"

mv "$tmpfile" "$PORTS_FILE"

if [[ $changed -eq 1 ]]; then
  /usr/bin/caddy reload --config /etc/caddy/Caddyfile 2>/dev/null || true
fi
